==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sweetmeat
<hw>Sweet"meat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Fruit
preserved with sugar, as peaches, pears, melons, nuts, orange peel,
etc.; -- usually in the plural; a confect; a confection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The paint used in making patent leather.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A boat shell (<spn>Crepidula
fornicata</spn>) of the American coast.</def> <mark>[Local,
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sweetness</ent>⟦br⟧
